/* ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   i18n for the declaude docs site.

   - LANGS: the languages offered in the picker (code + native label).
   - SNIPPETS: code/command blocks — shared verbatim across every language.
   - STRINGS: key-major dictionary; each key maps every language to its text.
     English (`en`) is the source of truth; `t()` falls back to it when a
     translation is missing, so adding a new language = fill in what you can
     and the rest stays readable.

   Light markup is allowed inside translated prose and rendered by <RichText>:
     **bold**, `code`, [label](url)
   ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

